{"reasoning":"1. The essential problem in the query is to identify the strongest, legally relevant European Convention (ECHR) articles that could be raised before the ECtHR concerning the central facts: removal of children from parental care and severe restrictions on family contact due to parental mental illness, involving emergency and then ongoing public care, procedural concerns, and possibly the right to family life. \n\n2. The only candidate presented ([0]) is \"European Union Structure and Governance.\" This candidate summarises the foundational aspects of the EU, its institutions, and governance systems, and refers to EU legislative processes. However, the central injury and legal questions in the user query concern rights protected by the European Convention on Human Rights (ECHR), specifically articles regarding private and family life (Article 8), potential procedural protections (Article 6), and possibly non-discrimination (Article 14). The structure and governance of the European Union is not relevant to ECtHR case law or Convention articles, nor does it contain the specific information needed to resolve Convention rights issues presented in the query. Therefore, this document is irrelevant to the key legal issues.\n\nThus, the candidate does not provide the information needed to answer the question and traversing into it would be wholly off-path from the required legal topics.","ranking":[0],"relevance_scores":[[0,0]]}
