ncated]  \n\n---\n\n## CANDIDATES\n\nHere are the candidates, each is identified by a unique `node_id` provided at the very start in [] (e.g., [0]).\n\n[0]. EU Protocols: Rights, Procedures, and Governance. This subtree addresses questions about the rights and freedoms protected by EU Protocols, the legal and procedural framework for their application, court and institutional procedures (including ECHR structure and case processing), legal governance and ratification, withdrawal processes, Article 2 declarations, and depositary roles. Use this subtree for queries on protocol rights, application and compliance procedures, court structure, treaty ratification, withdrawal requirements, and the legal responsibilities of EU member states and institutions.. Key topics: EU Protocol rights and freedoms; ECHR court procedures; Protocol application processes; Legal governance and ratification; Withdrawal from EU Convention; Article 2 declarations; Depositary roles and notifications. 6 direct children. 345 leaf passages\n\n[1]. EU Convention Emergency Powers. Provides information on the legal frameworks and procedures for suspending obligations under the EU Convention during emergencies, including Article 15 derogation, notification protocols, limits on emergency powers, and rights that remain protected. Useful for queries about legal exceptions, emergency processes, and non-derogable rights under the EU Convention.. Key topics: Article 15 derogation; emergency powers; EU Convention obligations; notification requirements; non-derogable rights; war-time legal exceptions. 1 direct children. 4 leaf passages\n\n[2]. EU Protocol Article 28 Committees Overview. Provides detailed information on the structure, authority, and decision-making processes of committees established under Article 28 of the EU Protocol. Useful for queries about committee roles, competence, voting rules, and procedures for handling Article 34 applications within the EU legal framework.. Key topics: EU Protocol Article 28; Committee competence; Decision-making authority; Unanimous voting; Article 34 applications; Legal procedures; Committee structure. 1 direct children. 3 leaf passages\n\n[3]. Striking Out Applications under EU Protocol Art. 37. Provides information on the legal procedures, criteria, and exceptions for striking out and restoring applications under Article 37 of the EU Protocol. Useful for questions about application dismissal, restoration processes, Court decision-making, applicant intent, and human rights considerations in the context of EU legal proceedings.. Key topics: EU Protocol Article 37; striking out applications; restoring applications; Court procedures; applicant intent; case resolution; human rights exceptions. 1 direct children. 3 leaf passages\n\n[4]. EU Family Law Protections. Provides information on legal rights and responsibilities of spouses and parents under EU law, especially regarding equality in marriage, divorce, and child welfare as defined by Protocol 7 Article 5. Useful for queries about spousal equality, division of marital responsibilities, and state obligations to children in EU member states.. Key topics: EU Protocol 7 Article 5; spousal equality; marriage rights; divorce law; parental responsibilities; child welfare provisions. 1 direct children. 2 leaf passages\n\n[5]. Protocol 16 Article 1(3) Request Procedures. Guidance on the procedural and substantive requirements for courts or tribunals making requests under Article 1(3) of Protocol 16 to the European Convention on Human Rights, including necessary justifications, legal and factual background, and court procedures.. Key topics: Protocol 16 Article 1(3); European Convention on Human Rights; request requirements; court procedures; legal background; factual background. 1 direct children. 1 leaf passages\n\n\n\n---\n\n## YOUR EVALUATION TASK\n1.  First, identify the essential problem in the query.\n2.  Think step by step to reason about why each candidate is relevant or ir