rder of the candidates.\n* `relevance_scores`: This must be an **array of arrays** where each inner array contains [node_id, relevance_score]. For example: [[0, 85], [1, 92], [2, 73]].\n\n---\n\nPrompt ID: 9307509 (Ignore this, it is just for watermarking purposes)\n\n## YOUR RESPONSE\n"
Response:
{"reasoning":"1. Essential problem: The core legal injury in the facts is the forced intervention by social welfare authorities into family life—namely, the emergency and subsequent full removal of K.'s children (M. and J.) from her care and the restriction of her parental contact, due to concerns over her mental health—and potentially associated procedural defects (lack of due process, inability to challenge or be heard before care orders). The essential problem is state interference with family life and access to children, and whether there has been an effective legal remedy.\n\n2. Candidate analysis:\n- [0] 'EU Protocol Section I Art. 13 Right to an effective remedy' is a section title or heading only. It does not contain substantive information, only the name of the right. It does not provide the operative convention language or any specifics that can guide a legal evaluation.\n- [1] 'EU Protocol Section I Art. 13(1) Right to an effective remedy Everyone whose rights and freedoms as set forth in this Convention are violated shall have an effective remedy before a national authority notwithstanding that the violation has been committed by persons acting in an official capacity.' This contains the full operative provision of the right to an effective remedy. This is highly relevant since a key procedural issue in the case facts is whether the applicants (K. and others) had access to a meaningful remedy to challenge the removal of their children, the emergency orders, or the restrictions on contact. Article 13 may be cited as a primary or secondary basis for a claim in such a case, especially if the applicants were denied the opportunity to be heard prior to the decisions, as described in the facts.\n\nConclusion: Only [1] contains substantive, directly relevant Convention text. [0] is a heading and provides no details and is thus not relevant per the definition.","ranking":[1,0],"relevance_scores":[[0,10],[1,95]]}
